Adaro, Astra, Bank Rakyat, Indocement: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-07-29T01:48:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/adaro-astra-bank-rakyat-indocement-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  fell 0.7 percent to 4,145.83.  PT Adaro Energy (ADRO IJ): Coal production at the nation’s
second-largest producer rose 19 percent in the second quarter to
12.2 million metric tons and sales gained 27 percent to a record
13.1 million tons, the company said in an e-mailed statement.
Adaro advanced 2.9 percent to 2,675 rupiah.  PT Astra International (ASII IJ): Indonesia’s biggest
automotive retailer’s second-quarter net income rose 25 percent
from a year earlier to 4.3 trillion rupiah ($505.5 million), the
company said in a statement to the stock exchange. Astra
declined 4.3 percent to 71,750 rupiah.  PT Bank Central Asia (BBCA IJ): The lender’s first-half net
income rose 20 percent to 4.8 trillion rupiah from a year
earlier, the company said. Bank Central Asia,  Indonesia ’s
largest bank by market value, fell 1.8 percent to 8,200 rupiah.  PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BBRI IJ): The company’s first-
half net income rose to 6.78 trillion rupiah from 4.32 trillion
rupiah a year earlier, the lender said in a statement published
in Bisnis Indonesia. Bank Rakyat, the nation’s second-largest
bank by assets, slid 1.5 percent to 6,800 rupiah.  PT Bank Mandiri (BMRI IJ): The bank’s first-half net income
rose to 6.3 trillion rupiah from a year ago, Finance Director
Pahala Mansury said. Mandiri, the nation’s biggest bank by
assets, retreated 1.9 percent to 7,900 rupiah.  PT Garuda Indonesia (GIAA IJ): Indonesia’s largest carrier
posted a 187.3 billion rupiah net loss in the first half,
compared with profit of 55.69 billion rupiah a year earlier, the
company said in a statement published in  Bisnis Indonesia .
Revenue in the six months ended June 30 rose to 11.21 trillion
rupiah from 7.76 trillion rupiah, it said. Garuda climbed 2
percent to 520 rupiah.  PT Indocement Tunggal Prakarsa (INTP IJ): The company’s
first-half net income rose to 1.72 trillion rupiah from 1.64
trillion rupiah a year earlier, the company said in a statement
published in Bisnis Indonesia. Indocement, Indonesia’s second-
largest cement producer, fell 3.1 percent to 15,900 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
